{"date":"Wed, 12 Feb 2020 00:00:00 GMT","img_url":"https://english.khabarhub.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/BP_Koirala_Cancer_Hospital.jpg","keywords":["corona","mandatory","would","hospital","test","makes","khabarhub","koirala","to","cancer","the","patients","bp","for","of","treatment"],"summary":"BP Koirala Cancer Hospital makes corona test mandatoryBP Koirala Memorial Cancer Hospital in Chitwan (File Photo)CHITWAN: The Bharatpur-based BP Koirala Memorial Cancer Hospital has made PCR test mandatory for cancer patients as well.\nThe hospital said it would initiate cancer treatment of the patients after carrying out PCR test.\nThe hospital decided to make the coronavirus test mandatory for all cancer survivor patients prior to the treatment in view of rapid transmission of the virus of late.\nAs many as 42 health workers and staff of the hospital have been so far diagnosed with coronavirus infection.\nNormally the hospital has been providing cancer treatment service to 700-800 patients daily but now only one-fourth of the number are visiting the hospital for treatment, the hospital administration said.","text":"BP Koirala Cancer Hospital makes corona test mandatory\n\nBP Koirala Memorial Cancer Hospital in Chitwan (File Photo)\n\nCHITWAN: The Bharatpur-based BP Koirala Memorial Cancer Hospital has made PCR test mandatory for cancer patients as well.\n\nThe hospital said it would initiate cancer treatment of the patients after carrying out PCR test.\n\nThe hospital decided to make the coronavirus test mandatory for all cancer survivor patients prior to the treatment in view of rapid transmission of the virus of late.\n\nExecutive Director of the hospital Dr Dej Kumar Gautam said providing treatment to coronavirus-infected patients with other patients would accelerate chances for virus transmission to the hospital staff and patients.\n\nHe stated it would not be otherwise to initiate cancer treatment only following liberation from coronavirus which normally takes two-week-long medical interventions.\n\n\u201cSince the mortality rate would likely go up by 25 to 35 percent while treating cancer survivors with corona patients, PCR test of the people coming for cancer treatment is a must\u201d, he said.\n\nThose diagnosed with corona infection would only be treated after they test negative for the virus, Dr Gautam maintained.\n\nLikewise, the hospital has enforced a rule of \u2018one patient, one caregiver\u2019 to avoid the transmission of virus infection.\n\nAs many as 42 health workers and staff of the hospital have been so far diagnosed with coronavirus infection. Seven among them have recovered.\n\nNormally the hospital has been providing cancer treatment service to 700-800 patients daily but now only one-fourth of the number are visiting the hospital for treatment, the hospital administration said.","title":"BP Koirala Cancer Hospital makes corona test mandatory - Khabarhub","url":"http://english.khabarhub.com/2020/02/124402/","video":[]}
